942
00:52:15.794 --> 00:52:19.654
All these arrangements qualify as forced labor under your

943
00:52:19.694 --> 00:52:20.314
definition.

944
00:52:21.684 --> 00:52:25.454
The question is, why do people willingly sign up for these

945
00:52:25.494 --> 00:52:29.434
jobs? And the reason they do so is because

946
00:52:29.494 --> 00:52:32.954
the alternatives are often far worse.

947
00:52:35.094 --> 00:52:38.654
Third, and most importantly, laws such as

948
00:52:38.714 --> 00:52:42.514
these often end up exacerbating the

949
00:52:42.594 --> 00:52:44.814
very problem they seek to solve.

950
00:52:45.994 --> 00:52:49.134
As the former World Bank chief economist, Kaushik Basu,

951
00:52:49.834 --> 00:52:53.534
points out, this is an area where prescription

952
00:52:53.614 --> 00:52:56.914
has outstripped analysis by a wide margin.

953
00:52:58.374 --> 00:53:02.354
So let's take the example of child labor, which is very much a part

954
